# Content Patterns

Write in **Australian English**: colour, organisation, behaviour, recognise, catalogue.

## MDX Articles (`content/articles/`)

```yaml
---
title: "The Case for Boring UX"
date: "2025-01-15"
teaser: "One sentence that makes someone want to read the whole thing."
tags: ["ux", "design", "product"]
---
```

- Route: `/thinking-about/{slug}`
- Slug = filename without `.mdx`
- Use `UXDemoBox` for interactive good/bad UX demos within articles

## MDX Case Studies (`content/projects/`)

```yaml
---
title: "Project Title"
role: "Principal Product Designer"
timeline: "Q3 2024 – Q1 2025"
company: "Company Name"
tags: ["product", "design-systems"]
---
```

- Route: `/tinkered-and-delivered/{slug}`
- Only created when the matching entry in `projects.json` has `"locked": false`

## JSON Manifests

### polls.json
```json
{ "id": "pineapple", "question": "...", "optionA": "...", "optionB": "...", "kimsAnswer": "a", "quip": "..." }
```

### noodling.json
```json
{ "id": "...", "type": "sticky"|"image"|"video"|"link"|"embed", "x": 0, "y": 0, "rotation": -2, "tags": [] }
```
- `"sticky"` adds: `content`, `color` (campfire palette name)
- `"image"/"video"/"link"` adds: `title`, `thumbnail`, `link`, `width?`
- `"embed"` adds: `title`, `embedUrl`, `width?`

### projects.json
```json
{ "slug": "project-slug", "title": "...", "teaser": "...", "locked": false }
```

## Adding Content

| Content type | How |
|---|---|
| New article | Create MDX in `content/articles/` with required frontmatter |
| New case study | Add to `projects.json` + create MDX in `content/projects/` |
| New poll | Add object to `content/polls.json` |
| New noodling card | Add object to `content/noodling.json` with `x`, `y`, `rotation` |
| New illustration | Export from Procreate → drop in `public/illustrations/{name}.png` |
